commentTextItems.html: and that's the victory! A full toss is clipped out to deep midwicket. They scamper back for the second, Handscomb brings the dive out

commentPostTextItems.html: Australia win by eight wickets and that's four wins in a row now. A very efficient run chase, led by Aaron Finch's century which Shaun Marsh supporting him well. It never really looked in doubt from a long way out. Earlier, Australia's spinners did a very good job on a slow surface as Pakistan never really got away from them with the bat. Haris Sohail made a good hundred, and there was a bit of a dart in the final five overs, but there was a lack of power for much of the innings. Australia's one-day momentum continues to build nicely. Who'd have thought it a month ago? There are four more matches in this series, the next of them on Sunday so it's a quick turnaround.

Shoaib Malik "Early strikes were missing from our side. Must say the way Finch and Marsh batted, they controlled the innings and took it deep. You can always make things better, we gave away some extra singles when batsmen are set. A few areas to improve. I would like to congratulate Haris on scoring a hundred coming back from injury. A great sign for Pakistan cricket."

Aaron Finch (who is also Man of the Match) "It was to chase down that total, was pretty daunting but it played really well in the second half. Nice to hit a few in the middle. I think doing it two-down was a real positive for us. There's a been a few times recently where it might have got to 6 or 7 down. The way Shaun played was a huge bonus to take the pressure off me. Just great to get the win. There's still room for improvement but nice to get four wins in a row. Nice that people are seeing the rewards for some hard work."
That just about wraps things up for today. Thanks for staying with us during the earlier problems. We'll be back on Sunday. Until then, from Gnasher and Alex, it's goodbye.

commentTextItems.html: short of a length, goes for the pull and gets a big top edge which flies back over the keeper...just two needed now
back of a length outside off, pushed into the covers without any real timing...they are doing it in singles
goes for the yorker, it's a low full toss, just a single out to deep midwicket
full outside off, Handscomb in a very odd position as he fetches it down to long leg
short outside off, Marsh is almost through his shot too early and lobs it down the ground to long-off
big full toss on the pads, swung to deep midwicket

commentPreTextItems.html: Zeeshan: "Gnasher couldnt watch the whole match but was batting underlights easy than at day time..i think bowl is coming onto the bat nicely." Perhaps a little, yes

commentTextItems.html: poor ball, full down the leg side...Rizwan suggests it clipped the pad. Nope, missed everything
big full toss, again Handscomb moving outside leg, driven to deep cover
follows the batsman as he moves outside leg, shovelled into the leg side and sluggish fielding allows a second
full outside leg stump, clubbed on the bounce to deep midwicket
back of a length slower ball, Handscomb leans back, trying to give himself some room, drives to point

commentPostTextItems.html: Ghalib: "To all the cricket fans who still watching this match... Believe me next 4 matches will not be different from this one." That's, urm, something to look forward to

dismissalText.commentary: Umar Akmal c Finch b Coulter-Nile 48 (50b 0x4 3x6) SR: 96

dismissalComment.html: he holes out to mid off! Caught by Finch running back! This was a strange shot straight after drinks. It was a length ball, he tried to club this down the ground from the crease, he miscued slicing this high straight of mid off but he hit it straight up, Finch ran back a touch and took the catch well.
